column5: Stopped by the dock this morning to take a look at the awesome veiw.Water very low for this time off the year.Water should be at least halfway up the ramp.Not much moisture in the forecast.
That’s a narrow ramp from the picture at least, I can already think of my dad yelling at me backing in the boat
There's a ice cube floating in the picture,so it's not ice out yet.lol
Not that narrow have about 4" on each side of my trailer tires.lol.
[QUOTE=Eckohlt;6738669]There’s a ice cube floating in the picture,so it’s not ice out There's ice still here and there but our Temps are awesome.

Has the water levels come up at all in your area? Just wondering if we will be seeing low water throughout the area this spring? I was seeing some pics of Lac Suel and it looked very low as well, although i know they try to keep it lower in the spring and bring it up with spring rains..
Water was low with very little run off this spring and still have had no significant rain so it will be low unless we get a lot of rain.
A year ago we were looking at pictures of that doc and the water was about to go over it.

Would need a lot of rain to just bring it up to normal.Havd to hope for lots of moisture.buddg of mine has his trailed on seasonal spot in Sioux narrows and just got there today and said it's down 4 ft according levels on the dock there.
